{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01ETvaVATrnYcuQaCe9oqBHp","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Cinis — Lessons Learned\n     2→*Auto-read by Claude Code at session start via CLAUDE.md*\n     3→*Updated: S26 · March 25, 2026*\n     4→*Rule: Any mistake made twice gets added here immediately. Never delete old lessons — they repeat.*\n     5→\n     6→## Auth — Never Touch These\n     7→- lib/supabase.js uses plain createClient — localStorage sessions. DO NOT change.\n     8→- Auth pattern in dashboard.js: onAuthStateChange + hasSession ref guard ONLY.\n     9→- NEVER add getSession(). NEVER recreate pages/api/auth/callback.js. NEVER install @supabase/ssr.\n    10→- Google OAuth redirects directly to /dashboard — no server-side callback. Intentional.\n    11→- Before testing old accounts: DevTools → Application → Storage → Clear site data.\n    12→- pages/api/auth/callback.js was deleted in S24. Do not recreate it. Ever.\n    13→\n    14→## Files That Must Never Be Modified\n    15→- lib/memoryCompression.js — Haiku rolling memory. Hands off.\n    16→- lib/rateLimit.js — Rate limiting. Modifying breaks free/pro enforcement.\n    17→- pages/api/stripe/webhook.js — bodyParser: false required. Every attempt to improve this has broken it.\n    18→- lib/supabase.js — Auth config.\n    19→- onAuthStateChange pattern in dashboard.js — Do not refactor.\n    20→\n    21→## Terminal Protocol\n    22→- One terminal = one file domain. Concurrent edits = merge conflicts.\n    23→- Always run git fetch origin && git rebase origin/main before pushing with multiple terminals active.\n    24→- Build passing ≠ feature working. Solver 3 visual confirmation required.\n    25→- Never mark complete without npm run build first.\n    26→\n    27→## Launching Claude Code Correctly\n    28→- /model /compact /plugin /skills are Claude Code slash commands — NOT raw zsh.\n    29→- Launch first: cd ~/Documents/focusbuddy-app && claude --dangerously-skip-permissions\n    30→- Then run slash commands inside Claude Code.\n    31→- session_start.sh fires automatically via .claude/settings.json startup hook.\n    32→\n    33→## Colors — One Source of Truth\n    34→Coal #211A14 · Char #3E3228 · Ash #F5F0E3 · Hot Pool #FF6644 (PRIMARY) · Ember #E8321A (URGENCY ONLY) · Gold #FFB800 · Green #4CAF50 · Blue #3B8BD4\n    35→Hot Pool is default for ALL interactive elements. Ember is ONLY for delete, overdue, urgent CTAs.\n    36→\n    37→## Typography\n    38→Numbers/wordmark/timer: Sora · Everything else: Figtree · No other fonts.\n    39→\n    40→## Layout Constants\n    41→Sidebar: 106px wide · Content padding: 12px 14px · paddingBottom: 80px (FAB clearance) · Card radius: 10px standard, 8px compact\n    42→\n    43→## Transplant Rule\n    44→Mockup = spec. Terminal copies it wholesale. Does not interpret, approximate, or improve it.\n    45→Read mockup completely → replace section entirely → wire real data → build.\n    46→\n    47→## Dashboard Split (completed S26)\n    48→- components/tabs/ has 11 tab files + shared.js\n    49→- Each tab receives { user, profile } as props\n    50→- No tab imports FROM dashboard.js (circular dependency)\n    51→- Voice FAB + morning greeting stay in dashboard.js only\n    52→\n    53→## Supabase MCP\n    54→- execute_sql for SELECT/inspect · apply_migration for DDL with IF NOT EXISTS guards\n    55→- Always use supabaseAdmin (service role key) in API routes\n    56→- bills.amount must be numeric(10,2) — integer loses decimals\n    57→- progress_snapshots populated by daily cron — empty for new users is expected\n    58→\n    59→## Progress Snapshots\n    60→- Monthly = calendar month window. Weekly = rolling 7 days. SEPARATE fetches, SEPARATE AI prompts.\n    61→- Cron: /api/cron/progress-snapshot.js runs daily at midnight UTC.\n    62→\n    63→## Ralph\n    64→- Runs inside tmux. tail -f .ralph/logs/latest.log to watch.\n    65→- EXIT_SIGNAL must be in every PROMPT.md or ralph won't stop.\n    66→- T6 is UltraClaude/Ralph only. Never assign Cinis feature work to T6.\n    67→- ralph --reset-circuit if circuit breaker trips.\n    68→\n    69→## context7 MCP\n    70→- Use for Next.js, Supabase, Stripe, Twilio docs before implementing anything.\n    71→- Kills hallucinated API methods.\n    72→\n    73→## Known Recurring Mistakes\n    74→1. Slash commands in raw zsh — always launch claude first.\n    75→2. Patching symptoms — always find root cause before fixing.\n    76→3. Build pass ≠ visual correct — always Solver 3 after build.\n    77→4. Wrong color values — always reference the color table, never guess.\n    78→5. Circular imports — tab files must never import from dashboard.js.\n    79→6. Missing bodyParser:false — always check stripe/webhook.js after refactors near it.\n    80→\n    81→*Update immediately when a new pattern is discovered. Never delete old lessons.*\n    82→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fdbc200a-ad61-40f1-afb6-ec011de01e9b","uuid":"ee2fcfd2-530c-45c7-be96-3c501f09e7b3","timestamp":"2026-03-26T12:15:47.803Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ryanjohnson/Documents/focusbuddy-app/tasks/lessons.md","content":"# Cinis — Lessons Learned\n*Auto-read by Claude Code at session start via CLAUDE.md*\n*Updated: S26 · March 25, 2026*\n*Rule: Any mistake made twice gets added here immediately. Never delete old lessons — they repeat.*\n\n## Auth — Never Touch These\n- lib/supabase.js uses plain createClient — localStorage sessions. DO NOT change.\n- Auth pattern in dashboard.js: onAuthStateChange + hasSession ref guard ONLY.\n- NEVER add getSession(). NEVER recreate pages/api/auth/callback.js. NEVER install @supabase/ssr.\n- Google OAuth redirects directly to /dashboard — no server-side callback. Intentional.\n- Before testing old accounts: DevTools → Application → Storage → Clear site data.\n- pages/api/auth/callback.js was deleted in S24. Do not recreate it. Ever.\n\n## Files That Must Never Be Modified\n- lib/memoryCompression.js — Haiku rolling memory. Hands off.\n- lib/rateLimit.js — Rate limiting. Modifying breaks free/pro enforcement.\n- pages/api/stripe/webhook.js — bodyParser: false required. Every attempt to improve this has broken it.\n- lib/supabase.js — Auth config.\n- onAuthStateChange pattern in dashboard.js — Do not refactor.\n\n## Terminal Protocol\n- One terminal = one file domain. Concurrent edits = merge conflicts.\n- Always run git fetch origin && git rebase origin/main before pushing with multiple terminals active.\n- Build passing ≠ feature working. Solver 3 visual confirmation required.\n- Never mark complete without npm run build first.\n\n## Launching Claude Code Correctly\n- /model /compact /plugin /skills are Claude Code slash commands — NOT raw zsh.\n- Launch first: cd ~/Documents/focusbuddy-app && claude --dangerously-skip-permissions\n- Then run slash commands inside Claude Code.\n- session_start.sh fires automatically via .claude/settings.json startup hook.\n\n## Colors — One Source of Truth\nCoal #211A14 · Char #3E3228 · Ash #F5F0E3 · Hot Pool #FF6644 (PRIMARY) · Ember #E8321A (URGENCY ONLY) · Gold #FFB800 · Green #4CAF50 · Blue #3B8BD4\nHot Pool is default for ALL interactive elements. Ember is ONLY for delete, overdue, urgent CTAs.\n\n## Typography\nNumbers/wordmark/timer: Sora · Everything else: Figtree · No other fonts.\n\n## Layout Constants\nSidebar: 106px wide · Content padding: 12px 14px · paddingBottom: 80px (FAB clearance) · Card radius: 10px standard, 8px compact\n\n## Transplant Rule\nMockup = spec. Terminal copies it wholesale. Does not interpret, approximate, or improve it.\nRead mockup completely → replace section entirely → wire real data → build.\n\n## Dashboard Split (completed S26)\n- components/tabs/ has 11 tab files + shared.js\n- Each tab receives { user, profile } as props\n- No tab imports FROM dashboard.js (circular dependency)\n- Voice FAB + morning greeting stay in dashboard.js only\n\n## Supabase MCP\n- execute_sql for SELECT/inspect · apply_migration for DDL with IF NOT EXISTS guards\n- Always use supabaseAdmin (service role key) in API routes\n- bills.amount must be numeric(10,2) — integer loses decimals\n- progress_snapshots populated by daily cron — empty for new users is expected\n\n## Progress Snapshots\n- Monthly = calendar month window. Weekly = rolling 7 days. SEPARATE fetches, SEPARATE AI prompts.\n- Cron: /api/cron/progress-snapshot.js runs daily at midnight UTC.\n\n## Ralph\n- Runs inside tmux. tail -f .ralph/logs/latest.log to watch.\n- EXIT_SIGNAL must be in every PROMPT.md or ralph won't stop.\n- T6 is UltraClaude/Ralph only. Never assign Cinis feature work to T6.\n- ralph --reset-circuit if circuit breaker trips.\n\n## context7 MCP\n- Use for Next.js, Supabase, Stripe, Twilio docs before implementing anything.\n- Kills hallucinated API methods.\n\n## Known Recurring Mistakes\n1. Slash commands in raw zsh — always launch claude first.\n2. Patching symptoms — always find root cause before fixing.\n3. Build pass ≠ visual correct — always Solver 3 after build.\n4. Wrong color values — always reference the color table, never guess.\n5. Circular imports — tab files must never import from dashboard.js.\n6. Missing bodyParser:false — always check stripe/webhook.js after refactors near it.\n\n*Update immediately when a new pattern is discovered. Never delete old lessons.*\n","numLines":82,"startLine":1,"totalLines":82}}}
