{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DuCdhbFa2rFVXhwDcxW5sf","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→import Anthropic from '@anthropic-ai/sdk'\n     2→import { createClient } from '@supabase/supabase-js'\n     3→import { buildPersonaPrompt } from '../../lib/persona'\n     4→import { compressAndSaveMemory } from '../../lib/memoryCompression'\n     5→import { checkDailyRateLimit, rateLimitErrorResponse } from '../../lib/rateLimit'\n     6→\n     7→const anthropic = new Anthropic({ apiKey: process.env.ANTHROPIC_API_KEY })\n     8→\n     9→function getAdminClient() {\n    10→  const url = process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL\n    11→  const key = process.env.SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY\n    12→  console.log('[checkin] admin client key prefix:', key?.slice(0, 20))\n    13→  console.log('[checkin:client] url present:', !!url, '| service key present:', !!key)\n    14→  return createClient(url, key)\n    15→}\n    16→\n    17→// ── Tool definitions ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n    18→\n    19→const PERSONA_VOICE_INSTRUCTION = `PERSONA VOICE — CRITICAL. You must write in the exact voice of the user's persona blend. Examples of how each persona actually sounds:\n    20→\n    21→DRILL_SERGEANT: \"Dentist done. Insurance call, project email, walk — all overdue. Pick one. Go.\" Short sentences. No praise. Imperative. No questions.\n    22→COACH: \"Good momentum on the dentist call. You've got three things stacking up — insurance, project email, walk. Which one moves the needle most right now?\"\n    23→HYPE_PERSON: \"YES! Dentist call knocked out! Now we're cooking. Three more on the list — insurance, project email, walk. Which one are we CRUSHING next?!\"\n    24→THINKING_PARTNER: \"You got the dentist call done — what made that one easier to start? You've got insurance, project email, and your walk still open. What's actually in the way of the next one?\"\n    25→STRATEGIST: \"Dentist: complete. Three open: insurance call, project email, 30min walk. Highest consequence item is insurance. Recommend starting there. Confirm?\"\n    26→EMPATH: \"Really glad you got the dentist call done — that one takes courage. Three things still open. How are you feeling about tackling the next one?\"\n    27→\n    28→If the user's primary persona is drill_sergeant, write like the DRILL_SERGEANT example. Do not soften. Do not add warmth unless coach is in the blend. Commit fully to the voice.`\n    29→\n    30→const TOOL_USE_RULES = `TOOL USE RULES — CRITICAL:\n    31→When the user confirms a time, date, or scheduling decision during conversation, you MUST immediately call the appropriate tool — do not just acknowledge it conversationally. Examples:\n    32→- User says \"let's do 6pm\" → call reschedule_task with due_time = 6pm today\n    33→- User says \"add that to my list\" → call create_task immediately\n    34→- User says \"mark that done\" → call complete_task immediately\n    35→- User says \"push it to tomorrow\" → call reschedule_task with tomorrow's date\n    36→Never say \"I'll add that\" or \"I've scheduled that\" without actually calling the tool. Talk is not action. Use the tool.\n    37→\n    38→TIME CONVERSION — MANDATORY:\n    39→All datetime values in tool calls must be in UTC (ISO 8601). The user's local time and UTC offset are in the context above.\n    40→Convert before calling: user says \"6pm\" → look up their UTC offset → compute UTC time → use that in the tool call.\n    41→WRONG: due_time: \"2026-03-24T18:00:00.000Z\" when user is UTC-5 and says \"6pm\" (that would show as 1pm local)\n    42→RIGHT: due_time: \"2026-03-24T23:00:00.000Z\" (18:00 local + 5 hours = 23:00 UTC)\n    43→\n    44→FINANCE RULES — MANDATORY:\n    45→When the user asks about their finances, bills, spending, or daily budget — always call get_bills, get_daily_number, or log_spend before responding. Never estimate or guess financial figures. Always get live data. Examples:\n    46→- User says \"how much have I spent today?\" → call get_daily_number first\n    47→- User says \"what bills are coming up?\" → call get_bills first\n    48→- User says \"I just spent $50 on coffee\" → call log_spend immediately\n    49→- User says \"can I afford this?\" → call get_daily_number to check remaining budget`\n    50→\n    51→const TOOLS = [\n    52→  {\n    53→    name: 'reschedule_task',\n    54→    description: 'Reschedule a task to a specific date and time. Use this when confirming a task moves to tomorrow or a specific time.',\n    55→    input_schema: {\n    56→      type: 'object',\n    57→      properties: {\n    58→        task_id: { type: 'string', description: 'The task ID to reschedule' },\n    59→        scheduled_for: { type: 'string', description: 'ISO datetime string for when to schedule' },\n    60→        due_time: { type: 'string', description: 'ISO datetime string for the due time, if specified' }\n    61→      },\n    62→      required: ['task_id', 'scheduled_for']\n    63→    }\n    64→  },\n    65→  {\n    66→    name: 'update_task_time',\n    67→    description: 'Update a task due time based on user input during check-in',\n    68→    input_schema: {\n    69→      type: 'object',\n    70→      properties: {\n    71→        task_id: { type: 'string' },\n    72→        due_time: { type: 'string', description: 'ISO datetime string' }\n    73→      },\n    74→      required: ['task_id', 'due_time']\n    75→    }\n    76→  },\n    77→  {\n    78→    name: 'schedule_morning_checkin',\n    79→    description: \"Schedule the morning check-in notification. Call this when telling the user you'll check in at a specific time.\",\n    80→    input_schema: {"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fdbc200a-ad61-40f1-afb6-ec011de01e9b","uuid":"eb3223e0-d0d6-4dc0-b295-84bd7955a89e","timestamp":"2026-03-26T12:16:02.709Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ryanjohnson/Documents/focusbuddy-app/pages/api/checkin.js","content":"import Anthropic from '@anthropic-ai/sdk'\nimport { createClient } from '@supabase/supabase-js'\nimport { buildPersonaPrompt } from '../../lib/persona'\nimport { compressAndSaveMemory } from '../../lib/memoryCompression'\nimport { checkDailyRateLimit, rateLimitErrorResponse } from '../../lib/rateLimit'\n\nconst anthropic = new Anthropic({ apiKey: process.env.ANTHROPIC_API_KEY })\n\nfunction getAdminClient() {\n  const url = process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL\n  const key = process.env.SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY\n  console.log('[checkin] admin client key prefix:', key?.slice(0, 20))\n  console.log('[checkin:client] url present:', !!url, '| service key present:', !!key)\n  return createClient(url, key)\n}\n\n// ── Tool definitions ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nconst PERSONA_VOICE_INSTRUCTION = `PERSONA VOICE — CRITICAL. You must write in the exact voice of the user's persona blend. Examples of how each persona actually sounds:\n\nDRILL_SERGEANT: \"Dentist done. Insurance call, project email, walk — all overdue. Pick one. Go.\" Short sentences. No praise. Imperative. No questions.\nCOACH: \"Good momentum on the dentist call. You've got three things stacking up — insurance, project email, walk. Which one moves the needle most right now?\"\nHYPE_PERSON: \"YES! Dentist call knocked out! Now we're cooking. Three more on the list — insurance, project email, walk. Which one are we CRUSHING next?!\"\nTHINKING_PARTNER: \"You got the dentist call done — what made that one easier to start? You've got insurance, project email, and your walk still open. What's actually in the way of the next one?\"\nSTRATEGIST: \"Dentist: complete. Three open: insurance call, project email, 30min walk. Highest consequence item is insurance. Recommend starting there. Confirm?\"\nEMPATH: \"Really glad you got the dentist call done — that one takes courage. Three things still open. How are you feeling about tackling the next one?\"\n\nIf the user's primary persona is drill_sergeant, write like the DRILL_SERGEANT example. Do not soften. Do not add warmth unless coach is in the blend. Commit fully to the voice.`\n\nconst TOOL_USE_RULES = `TOOL USE RULES — CRITICAL:\nWhen the user confirms a time, date, or scheduling decision during conversation, you MUST immediately call the appropriate tool — do not just acknowledge it conversationally. Examples:\n- User says \"let's do 6pm\" → call reschedule_task with due_time = 6pm today\n- User says \"add that to my list\" → call create_task immediately\n- User says \"mark that done\" → call complete_task immediately\n- User says \"push it to tomorrow\" → call reschedule_task with tomorrow's date\nNever say \"I'll add that\" or \"I've scheduled that\" without actually calling the tool. Talk is not action. Use the tool.\n\nTIME CONVERSION — MANDATORY:\nAll datetime values in tool calls must be in UTC (ISO 8601). The user's local time and UTC offset are in the context above.\nConvert before calling: user says \"6pm\" → look up their UTC offset → compute UTC time → use that in the tool call.\nWRONG: due_time: \"2026-03-24T18:00:00.000Z\" when user is UTC-5 and says \"6pm\" (that would show as 1pm local)\nRIGHT: due_time: \"2026-03-24T23:00:00.000Z\" (18:00 local + 5 hours = 23:00 UTC)\n\nFINANCE RULES — MANDATORY:\nWhen the user asks about their finances, bills, spending, or daily budget — always call get_bills, get_daily_number, or log_spend before responding. Never estimate or guess financial figures. Always get live data. Examples:\n- User says \"how much have I spent today?\" → call get_daily_number first\n- User says \"what bills are coming up?\" → call get_bills first\n- User says \"I just spent $50 on coffee\" → call log_spend immediately\n- User says \"can I afford this?\" → call get_daily_number to check remaining budget`\n\nconst TOOLS = [\n  {\n    name: 'reschedule_task',\n    description: 'Reschedule a task to a specific date and time. Use this when confirming a task moves to tomorrow or a specific time.',\n    input_schema: {\n      type: 'object',\n      properties: {\n        task_id: { type: 'string', description: 'The task ID to reschedule' },\n        scheduled_for: { type: 'string', description: 'ISO datetime string for when to schedule' },\n        due_time: { type: 'string', description: 'ISO datetime string for the due time, if specified' }\n      },\n      required: ['task_id', 'scheduled_for']\n    }\n  },\n  {\n    name: 'update_task_time',\n    description: 'Update a task due time based on user input during check-in',\n    input_schema: {\n      type: 'object',\n      properties: {\n        task_id: { type: 'string' },\n        due_time: { type: 'string', description: 'ISO datetime string' }\n      },\n      required: ['task_id', 'due_time']\n    }\n  },\n  {\n    name: 'schedule_morning_checkin',\n    description: \"Schedule the morning check-in notification. Call this when telling the user you'll check in at a specific time.\",\n    input_schema: {","numLines":80,"startLine":1,"totalLines":1180}}}
